Q1) What is Python? What are the ways to install Python?
Ans: Python is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose programming language. It consists of huge amount of additional open-source libraries and which helps in taking care of common programming tasks, thus allowing us to focus on core functionality of the application.
Python can be installed from python.org or through any other IDE containing python based libraries like Anaconda.

Q2) What are code environments and types of code environments?
Ans: Code environment is a self contained environment used to develop, execute and test a code block.
They are of three types:
1)Text Editor - where code can be written and modified
2)Full IDE - provides comprehensive facilities for software development
3)Notebook Environments - interactive interface which helps in developing and analysing codes.
